n\nconsists in polynomial time Turing reductions from both BPol(G)- and\nBPol(G+)-separation to G-separation. This yields polynomial algorithms for key\nvariants of B{\\Sigma}1, including those equipped with the linear ordering and\npossibly the successor and/or the modular predicates.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 3 Oct 2022 14:02:25 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-10-04"}
